title: Factorial Modulo Prime
text:
Find $N!$modulo$P$.InputThe first line contains $T$ ($1 \le T \le 100,000$), the number of test cases.Each of the next $T$ lines contains two integers $N$ ($0 \le N \le 10^{11}$) and $P$ ($2 \le P \le 10^{11}$), where $P$ is a prime.OutputFor each $N$ and $P$, output $N!$modulo$P$.ConstraintsFor each input file, It is guaranteed that (the sum of $\sqrt{P}) \le 320000$.ExampleInput3
1000 9907
1000000 9999907
10000000000 99999999907Output4494
3354924
40583077821NoteProbably, $O(P)$ solutions will not pass.Intended solutions have a complexity of about $O(\sqrt{P} \log{P})$My solution runs in 0.5 seconds for each input file.
